'''Berqayel''' or '''Berkayel''' (برقايل) is one of the largest and the most historical towns in [[Akkar Governorate]] in northern [[Lebanon]]. Berkail is about 25&nbsp;km north Tripoli. Berkail is well known by its olive production and green fields. It is a [[Sunni]] Muslim community.<ref>{{cite web|title=Municipal and ikhtiyariah elections in Northern Lebanon |url=http://www.localiban.org/IMG/pdf/iiMonthly-Municip-Mar10-E92.pdf |publisher=The Monthly |accessdate=25 October 2016 |page=23 |date=March 2010 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603040803/http://www.localiban.org/IMG/pdf/iiMonthly-Municip-Mar10-E92.pdf |archivedate=3 June 2016 |df= }}</ref>

== Economy ==
Much of Berkail's population is employed by the Lebanese Army. Olives are the main agricultural product.{{Citation needed|date=October 2016}}
