The '''Hebrew Political Union''' ({{lang-el|Κόμμα Εβραϊκής Πολιτικής Ενώσεως}}) was a political party in [[Greece]] in the 1920s.

==History==
The party first contested national elections in 1926,<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen]] & Philip Stöver (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p834 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> when they won two seats in the [[Greek legislative election, 1926|parliamentary elections]] with 0.6% of the national vote.<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p839</ref> However, the party did not contest any further elections.<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p834</ref>

